Detailed Description

Implements vector data structure equipped with copy-on-write mechanism.

Implementation of the guts of the vector<> class this ensures backward binary compatibility and reduces code size. For performance reasons, we expose mStorage and mCount so these fields are set in stone.

Warning:
This class is not used directly. Vector should use instead.
 // Creates a VectorImpl
 VectorImpl vec_impl(sizeof(int), HAS_TRIVIAL_CTOR);
 
 // Appends five integers
 int32_t testItem = 2011;
 vec_impl.insertAt(testItem, size(), 5);
 
 // Replace the 3rd items (index is 2)
 int32_t testRep = 2012;
 vec_impl.replaceAt(testRep, 2);
 
 // Clear all items
 vec_impl.clear();
